ls0 ws0">Cross-Questioning the Man Born Blind </div><div class="t m14b x74 h4 y1a85 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">11. After again calling the son who had been blind, what demand did </div><div class="t m594 x71 h4 y1620 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Pharisees make? What did they say they knew? Verse 24. </div><div class="t m119f x74 h4 y1aca ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NorE.—In saying &quot;Give God the praise: we know that this man is a sinner,&quot; </div><div class="t m7a9 x71 h4 y629 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Pharisees really meant, Do not say again that this man gave you sight; </div><div class="t mb85 x71 h4 y1b49 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">it is God who has done this. </div><div class="t m827 x2a h5f y190a ff4 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[ 17 </div><div class="t m73b x2b h4 y190a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
